WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:34.340
[Amit Varma]: Uber, the way people interact with each other has been disrupted by Facebook and Twitter

00:00:34.340 --> 00:00:35.760
[Amit Varma]: and Instagram.

00:00:35.760 --> 00:00:39.040
[Amit Varma]: Entertainment has been disrupted by Netflix and Amazon Prime.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:44.840
[Amit Varma]: And everywhere, consumers and producers have both benefited enormously from this.

00:00:44.840 --> 00:00:50.180
[Amit Varma]: But here's the thing, this disruption has happened in most marketplaces, but not yet

00:00:50.180 --> 00:00:52.640
[Amit Varma]: in the political marketplace.

00:00:52.640 --> 00:00:54.680
[Amit Varma]: So here's a question worth asking.

00:00:54.680 --> 00:01:10.600
[Unknown]: Can politics be disrupted as well?

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:12.140
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the Scene and the Unseen.

00:01:12.140 --> 00:01:18.240
[Amit Varma]: My guest for today is Rajesh Jain, who will be talking about his new project, Dhanwapsi.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:23.180
[Amit Varma]: I've known Rajesh since early 2015, and he's most famously known for being one of the brains

00:01:23.180 --> 00:01:26.060
[Amit Varma]: behind Narendra Modi's rise to power.

00:01:26.060 --> 00:01:29.320
[Amit Varma]: But I saw a completely different side of Rajesh when I met him.

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:34.960
[Amit Varma]: He had gotten buyer's remorse in 2014 itself, and when I met him in 2015, was an articulate

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:40.400
[Amit Varma]: and vociferous critic of Modi, a man he had once supported for understandable reasons.

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:44.960
[Amit Varma]: But Rajesh had the intellectual honesty to change his mind about Modi, and the commitment

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:49.880
[Amit Varma]: to continue working on projects that were actually designed to get Modi out of power

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:52.980
[Amit Varma]: at considerable personal risk to himself.

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:57.360
[Amit Varma]: He hasn't spoken about this publicly much in the past, but we'll speak about some of

00:01:57.360 --> 00:02:01.340
[Amit Varma]: that on this episode, and we won't speak about certain parts of it.

00:02:01.340 --> 00:02:06.240
[Amit Varma]: And while this episode is supposed to be about Dhanwapsi, which is an insanely ambitious

00:02:06.240 --> 00:02:11.360
[Amit Varma]: and extremely interesting project he's on, I decided to dedicate only the second half

00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:16.360
[Amit Varma]: of the episode to that project, and spend the first half discussing why he supported

00:02:16.360 --> 00:02:20.540
[Amit Varma]: Modi to begin with, and what made him change his mind.

00:02:20.540 --> 00:02:25.100
[Amit Varma]: This is a really long episode, but it's fascinating, so do listen to the full thing, after a quick

00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:27.340
[Amit Varma]: commercial break.

